<p>I use Autowire annotation both in Controller and Validator class to inject DAO implementation object to the private fields. Strange is that in the first class it works and DAOImpl is injected to the controller's field and in the second it doesn,t work. I'm getting a NullPointerException every time i trying to use (not) injected object.I put both class to excatly the same package.</p>  <pre><code>@Controller public class HomeController {  //it works     @Autowired     private UsersDAO usersDAOImpl; ... } </code></pre>  <p>and Validator class in the same package:</p>  <pre><code>public class UserValidator implements Validator {  /it doesn't work, NPException when try to use usersDAOImpl object     @Autowired     private UsersDAO usersDAOImpl; ... } </code></pre>  <p>Error stack trace:</p>  <pre><code>SEVERE: Servlet.service() for servlet [appServlet] in context with path [/manager] threw exception [Request processing failed; nested exception is java.lang.NullPointerException] with root cause java.lang.NullPointerException     at com.project.manager.UserValidator.validate(UserValidator.java:40)     at com.project.manager.HomeController.addUser(HomeController.java:132)     at sun.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke0(Native Method)     at sun.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(Unknown Source)     at sun.reflect.DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(Unknown Source)     at java.lang.reflect.Method.invoke(Unknown Source)     at org.springframework.web.method.support.InvocableHandlerMethod.invoke(InvocableHandlerMethod.java:215)     at org.springframework.web.method.support.InvocableHandlerMethod.invokeForRequest(InvocableHandlerMethod.java:132)     at org.springframework.web.servlet.mvc.method.annotation.ServletInvocableHandlerMethod.invokeAndHandle(ServletInvocableHandlerMethod.java:104)     at org.springframework.web.servlet.mvc.method.annotation.RequestMappingHandlerAdapter.invokeHandleMethod(RequestMappingHandlerAdapter.java:745)     at org.springframework.web